definitions: happening or existing in the period immediately following childbirth
examples: She attended postnatal classes with her baby
The doctor scheduled a postnatal checkup

definitions: relating to or denoting the period following a surgical operation
examples: The patient experienced postoperative pain for several days
Postoperative care includes monitoring vital signs regularly

definitions: occurring in or relating to the period immediately after childbirth
examples: Many women experience postpartum depression after delivery
The hospital provides postpartum support groups

definitions: relating to or affecting the position of the body
examples: Poor postural habits can lead to back pain
The therapist recommended postural exercises for improvement

definitions: existing or occurring in the period following a war
examples: The postwar economy experienced rapid growth
Many postwar buildings were constructed quickly

definitions: suitable for drinking without harmful effects on health
examples: The village lacks access to potable water
We carried potable water supplies for the hike

definitions: having great power, influence, or effect in action
physically, chemically, or medicinally effective in concentrated form
examples: The politician made a potent argument for reform
His words had a potent impact on listeners
This medicine is particularly potent against infections
The laboratory uses potent chemicals for experiments

definitions: planted or grown in a pot or container
preserved or cooked in a sealed pot or jar
presented in shortened or summarized form
examples: She arranged potted plants on the windowsill
The office featured several potted palm trees
They served potted shrimp as an appetizer
Grandmother made potted meat for sandwiches
He gave a potted history of the company
The article was a potted version of the book

definitions: relating to or used for toilet training of young children
showing slight mental instability or eccentric behavior
examples: The toddler is learning potty training this month
She bought a colorful potty chair for her son
He's absolutely potty about collecting vintage cars
Don't mind her potty ideas about gardening

definitions: falling or flowing in a heavy, continuous stream
examples: We got caught in pouring rain without umbrellas
The pouring water overflowed the drainage system

definitions: crushed or ground into fine particles like dust
examples: She added powdered sugar to the cake frosting
The recipe calls for powdered ginger and cinnamon

definitions: having the texture or consistency of fine dry particles
examples: The old paint left a powdery residue when touched
Fresh snow created a powdery surface for skiing

definitions: operated or driven by a specified source of energy
examples: The factory uses solar powered equipment
Electric powered vehicles are becoming more common

definitions: unable to act or influence; lacking strength, authority, or resources
examples: She felt powerless to change the situation
The storm left thousands powerless without electricity

definitions: able to be done or put into practice successfully given circumstances
examples: The committee sought practicable solutions to traffic problems
Is it practicable to finish by the deadline?

definitions: expert or skilled as a result of experience or training
examples: Her practiced hands quickly assembled the device
He spoke with the practiced ease of a professional

definitions: expert or skilled as a result of experience or training
examples: The surgeon's practised movements inspired confidence
She gave a practised smile to the camera

definitions: dealing with things sensibly and realistically rather than theoretically
examples: She took a pragmatic approach to solving problems
His pragmatic nature helped in business negotiations

definitions: deserving approval and admiration for good qualities or actions
examples: Their praiseworthy efforts raised funds for charity
The student's praiseworthy dedication earned recognition

definitions: expressing warm approval or admiration of someone or something
examples: The teacher's praising comments motivated the students
Critics wrote praising reviews of the performance

definitions: giving moral advice in a tedious or self-righteous way
examples: His preachy tone annoyed everyone at dinner
The movie felt too preachy about environmental issues

definitions: not securely held; dependent on chance; dangerously uncertain
examples: The climber was in a precarious position
Their financial situation remains precarious

definitions: made of concrete cast in a mold before being transported
examples: The building used precast concrete panels
Precast stairs were delivered to the construction site

definitions: carried out as a preventive measure to avoid possible danger
examples: The school took precautionary measures against illness
Precautionary evacuations were ordered before the storm

definitions: preceding in time, order, or importance; going before
examples: The precedent conditions must be met first
This precedent case influenced future legal decisions

definitions: existing or coming before in time, order, or position
examples: The preceding chapter explained the basic concepts
Events in the preceding year influenced decisions

definitions: done, made, or acting suddenly without careful consideration
examples: His precipitate decision to quit surprised everyone
They warned against precipitate action in crisis

definitions: causing an event or situation to happen suddenly or prematurely
examples: The precipitating factors of conflict were identified
Her illness was the precipitating event for change

definitions: dangerously high or steep like a cliff face
done suddenly and without careful consideration of consequences
examples: The mountain trail follows a precipitous path
They faced a precipitous drop to the valley
The company experienced a precipitous decline in sales
Stock prices took a precipitous fall yesterday

definitions: relating to or denoting the stage before clinical testing begins
examples: The drug showed promise in preclinical studies
Preclinical research involved laboratory testing on animals

definitions: having developed certain abilities earlier than usual, especially in children
examples: The precocious child read novels at age five
Her precocious talent for music amazed teachers

definitions: formed before having evidence or experience; prejudged without examination
examples: She challenged their preconceived notions about poverty
Try to approach without preconceived ideas

definitions: relating to animals that kill and eat other animals
seeking to exploit or harm others for personal gain
examples: Hawks are predatory birds that hunt small mammals
The jungle has many predatory species
The company engaged in predatory pricing practices
She warned about predatory lending schemes

definitions: established or decided in advance rather than by later events
examples: The outcome seemed predetermined from the start
They followed a predetermined route through the city

definitions: able to be predicted or expected; behaving in expected ways
examples: His reaction was entirely predictable given the circumstances
The movie had a predictable ending

definitions: relating to or having the ability to predict future events
examples: The model has strong predictive power for outcomes
Predictive analytics help businesses plan ahead

definitions: made susceptible to or inclined toward something in advance
examples: Genetics may predispose individuals to certain conditions
He was predisposed to trust her judgment

definitions: present as the strongest or main element; having superior influence
examples: Blue was the predominant color in the painting
English is the predominant language in business

definitions: surpassing all others in quality or importance; very distinguished
examples: She became the preeminent authority on ancient texts
The museum holds a preeminent collection of art

definitions: serving to prevent something by acting first; done before others
examples: The military launched a preemptive strike
She took preemptive measures against criticism

definitions: existing at or from an earlier time before something else
examples: Insurance may not cover preexisting medical conditions
They built upon preexisting infrastructure

definitions: manufactured in sections beforehand for quick assembly on site
examples: They chose prefab housing for quick construction
The prefab modules arrived ready for assembly

definitions: more desirable or suitable than alternatives; to be preferred
examples: Fresh vegetables are preferable to canned ones
Is morning or afternoon preferable for the meeting?

definitions: giving advantage or priority to particular people or things
examples: Members receive preferential treatment at events
The company offers preferential rates to students

definitions: liked or wanted more than other alternatives
given special advantages or priority in treatment
examples: Coffee is her preferred morning beverage
This is the preferred method among experts
Preferred customers get early access to sales
The bank offers preferred shares to investors

definitions: relating to the front part of the brain's frontal lobe
examples: The prefrontal cortex controls executive functions
Damage to prefrontal areas affects decision making

definitions: relating to the period before written records began
examples: Scientists discovered prehistoric cave paintings
The museum displays prehistoric tools and artifacts

definitions: having or showing dislike or unfair treatment based on prejudice
examples: His prejudiced views prevented fair judgment
The jury must not be prejudiced against defendants

definitions: harmful to someone or something; tending to cause prejudice
examples: The leaked information was prejudicial to the case
They avoided prejudicial statements during negotiations

definitions: preceding or done in preparation for the main matter or business
examples: The team conducted preliminary research before starting
Preliminary results suggest positive outcomes
